### ============================================================
###  VetLoop.API — HTTP Test Suite
###  IDE: VS Code REST Client / JetBrains HTTP Client / Rider
###
###  USAGE:
###    1. Start the API:  dotnet run --project VetLoop.API
###    2. Run "Register" first to create the test user
###    3. Run "Login" and copy the returned token
###    4. Paste the token into @authToken below
###    5. Run the protected-route tests
### ============================================================

@host    = http://localhost:5166
@apiBase = {{host}}/api

# ── After a successful /login, paste the returned JWT here ────────────────────
@authToken = PASTE_JWT_HERE


# ==============================================================================
#  1. REGISTER — Create a new FarmOwner account
#     Expected: 201 Created  +  AuthResponseDto JSON
#     Note: Will return 409 Conflict if the email already exists.
# ==============================================================================

POST {{apiBase}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName":    "Admin Test Farm",
  "email":       "admin@testfarm.com",
  "password":    "Password123!",
  "phoneNumber": "+905551234567",
  "role":        1
}

###


# ==============================================================================
#  2. LOGIN — Authenticate and retrieve a fresh JWT
#     Expected: 200 OK  +  AuthResponseDto JSON
#     Copy the "token" value from the response → paste into @authToken above
# ==============================================================================

POST {{apiBase}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email":    "admin@testfarm.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

###


# ==============================================================================
#  3. LOGIN — Wrong password (negative test)
#     Expected: 401 Unauthorized  +  { "error": "Invalid email or password." }
# ==============================================================================

POST {{apiBase}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email":    "admin@testfarm.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword!"
}

###


# ==============================================================================
#  4. REGISTER — Attempt Admin self-registration (blocked)
#     Expected: 400 Bad Request  +  { "error": "Admin accounts cannot be self-registered." }
#     UserRole enum: Admin = 0, FarmOwner = 1, Veterinarian = 2, FarmWorker = 3
# ==============================================================================

POST {{apiBase}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName":    "Hacker Admin",
  "email":       "hacker@evil.com",
  "password":    "Password123!",
  "phoneNumber": null,
  "role":        0
}

###


# ==============================================================================
#  5. GET FARMS — Protected endpoint (requires valid JWT)
#     Paste the login token into @authToken at the top, then run this.
#     Expected: 200 OK  +  array of Farm objects
#     Without token → 401 Unauthorized
# ==============================================================================

GET {{apiBase}}/farms
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

###


# ==============================================================================
#  6. GET PETS — Protected endpoint (requires valid JWT)
#     Expected: 200 OK  +  array of Pet objects
# ==============================================================================

GET {{apiBase}}/pets
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

###


# ==============================================================================
#  7. DUPLICATE REGISTER — Same email (conflict test)
#     Expected: 409 Conflict  +  { "error": "An account with email '...' already exists." }
#     (Run AFTER step 1 has succeeded)
# ==============================================================================

POST {{apiBase}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName":    "Duplicate User",
  "email":       "admin@testfarm.com",
  "password":    "Password123!",
  "phoneNumber": null,
  "role":        1
}

###
